msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1270
msgid "Remove extrusion calibration gcode"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1271
msgid "Enable this to skip extrusion calibration when start printing."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1277
msgid "Scan first layer"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1278
msgid ""
"Enable this to enable the camera on printer to check the quality of first "
"layer."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1283
msgid "Enable spaghetti detector"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1284
msgid "enable the camera on printer to check spaghetti."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1289
msgid "G-code flavor"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1290
msgid ""
"Some G/M-code commands, including temperature control and others, are not "
"universal. Set this option to your printer's firmware to get a compatible "
"output. The \"No extrusion\" flavor prevents BambuStudio from exporting any "
"extrusion value at all."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1317
msgid "No extrusion"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1322
msgid "Label objects"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1323
msgid ""
"Enable this to add comments into the G-Code labeling print moves with what "
"object they belong to, which is useful for the Octoprint CancelObject "
"plugin. This settings is NOT compatible with Single Extruder Multi Material "
"setup and Wipe into Object / Wipe into Infill."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1332
msgid "Infill combination"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1334
msgid ""
"This feature allows to combine infill automatically, and speed up your print "
"by extruding thicker infill layers while preserving thin perimeters, thus "
"accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1340
msgid "Length of the infill anchor"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1342
msgid ""
"Connect an infill line to an internal perimeter with a short segment of an "
"additional perimeter. If expressed as percentage (example: 15%) it is "
"calculated over infill extrusion width. BambuStudio tries to connect two "
"close infill lines to a short perimeter segment. If no such perimeter "
"segment shorter than infill_anchor_max is found, the infill line is "
"connected to a perimeter segment at just one side and the length of the "
"perimeter segment taken is limited to this parameter, but no longer than "
"anchor_length_max. Set this parameter to zero to disable anchoring "
"perimeters connected to a single infill line."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1358
msgid "0 (no open anchors)"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1359 src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1383
msgid "1 mm"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1360 src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1384
msgid "2 mm"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1361 src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1385
msgid "5 mm"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1362 src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1386
msgid "10 mm"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1363 src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1387
msgid "1000 (unlimited)"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1369
msgid "Maximum length of the infill anchor"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1371
msgid ""
"Connect an infill line to an internal perimeter with a short segment of an "
"additional perimeter. If expressed as percentage (example: 15%) it is "
"calculated over infill extrusion width. BambuStudio tries to connect two "
"close infill lines to a short perimeter segment. If no such perimeter "
"segment shorter than this parameter is found, the infill line is connected "
"to a perimeter segment at just one side and the length of the perimeter "
"segment taken is limited to infill_anchor, but no longer than this "
"parameter. Set this parameter to zero to disable anchoring."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1382
msgid "0 (not anchored)"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1394
msgid "The extruder to use when printing infill."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1402
msgid ""
"Set this to a non-zero value to set a manual extrusion width for infill. If "
"left zero, default extrusion width will be used if set, otherwise 1.125 x "
"nozzle diameter will be used. You may want to use fatter extrudates to speed "
"up the infill and make your parts stronger. If expressed as percentage (for "
"example 90%) it will be computed over layer height."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1413
msgid "Infill overlap"
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1415
msgid ""
"This setting applies an additional overlap between infill and perimeters for "
"better bonding. Theoretically this shouldn't be needed, but backlash might "
"cause gaps. If expressed as percentage (example: 15%) it is calculated over "
"perimeter extrusion width."
msgstr ""

#: src/libslic3r/PrintConfig.cpp:1426
msgid "Speed for printing the internal fill. Set to zero for auto."
msgstr ""

